(Machine Learning versus Deep Learning: Choosing the Right Approach for Two Real-World Problems) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 636.0 Tm
(Machine learning and deep learning both learn from data, but they differ in how features are) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 612.0 Tm
(derived and how much data and computation each one needs. This report examines two) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 588.0 Tm
(examples from the lesson. The first is email spam detection, a simple machine learning problem.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 564.0 Tm
(The second is medical image analysis, a deep learning problem. For each example I describe a) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 540.0 Tm
(real-world application, explain why the chosen approach fits the problem, and explain why the) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 516.0 Tm
(other approach does not.) Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 460.0 Tm
(Simple Machine Learning: Email Spam Detection) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 430.0 Tm
(A widely used application is the spam filter that sits on a corporate email gateway and scores) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 406.0 Tm
(every inbound message before it reaches a mailbox. The filter reads a small set of) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 382.0 Tm
(human-understandable signals and decides whether the message is spam or legitimate.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 352.0 Tm
(Simple machine learning fits this problem well. The signal lives in a compact set of features that) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 328.0 Tm
(a person can name in advance: the presence of certain words, the reputation of the sender) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 304.0 Tm
(domain, the ratio of links to text, and the length of the message. An algorithm such as logistic) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 280.0 Tm
(regression or a decision tree can learn a reliable boundary from a few thousand labeled messages) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 256.0 Tm
(\(Sahami et al., 1998\). Training is fast, the model runs cheaply at high volume, and the result is) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 232.0 Tm
(interpretable. A security analyst can see which features flagged a message, which matters when a) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 208.0 Tm
(blocked email has to be justified to the business.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 178.0 Tm
(Deep learning is not suitable here. A neural network needs very large labeled datasets and far) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 154.0 Tm
(more computation to match the accuracy that a simple model already reaches on this structured,) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 130.0 Tm
(low-dimensional data \(Goodfellow et al., 2016\). Its ability to learn features automatically adds) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 106.0 Tm
(little value, because the useful features are already known and easy to extract. The network) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 82.0 Tm
(would also hide its reasoning inside layers of weights, and that loss of transparency is a real cost) Tj
ET
